  "prompt": "Will I get refund after preparation of chart for wait listed ticket?",
  "response": "In general, if you have a waitlisted train ticket and it does not get confirmed after the preparation of the final reservation chart, you are usually eligible for a refund. The refund process and rules can vary depending on the railway system and the country you are in, so it's important to check the specific policies applicable to your situation. If it's for the Indian Railways, typically:\n\n1. If an e-ticket remains waitlisted even after the preparation of the final chart, it is automatically canceled, and the refund is processed back to your account.\n2. For counter tickets, you generally need to go to a railway booking counter and file for a refund.\n\nAlways verify the current policies from the official railway website or customer service to get accurate and up-to-date information for your specific case.",
